<div>The following describes the Intel's employee handbook.</div>

<div>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Code of Conduct: It's a roadmap of how employees should act and it speaks to your company culture.
        </li>
        <li>
            Communications Policy: You are not allowed to use tools and websites not approved by Intel. Our website will
            be the main source of information to the general public. You are not allowed to talk to the press about matters
            related to the company without the company's permission.
        </li>
        <li>
            Nondiscrimination policy: We do not discriminate on the basis of the following:
            Age
            Race/color
            Religion
            Pregnancy
            Disability
        </li>
        <li>
            Compensation and benefits policy: You will be paid once every two weeks and you will be insured for health with a choice of three different policies.
            Your vacation days are 20 and we observe Federal Government's holidays. You will have 10 sick days.
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
